sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Authenticated client
    participant A as ASGI consumer
    participant P as PostgreSQL
    participant R as Redis fan-out
    participant H as History endpoint

    C->>A: send(client UUIDv4, room, text)
    A->>P: begin; DB-time status, participant, rate checks
    alt rejected policy or invalid input
        P-->>A: rollback / no row
        A-->>C: rejected 400/403/404/429
    else new valid command
        A->>P: insert unique(room, sender, client UUID)
        P-->>A: commit(server ID, cursor)
        A->>R: publish committed server ID once
        alt publish succeeds
            R-->>A: delivered
            A-->>C: accepted, delivery=live
        else publish fails or times out
            R--xA: unavailable
            A-->>C: accepted, delivery=degraded
            C->>H: fetch after last cursor
            H->>P: ordered authoritative history
            P-->>H: committed messages
            H-->>C: deduplicated cursor page
        end
    else idempotency key exists
        P-->>A: stored server ID and canonical payload
        alt payload identical
            A-->>C: prior accepted result; no republish
        else payload differs
            A-->>C: 409 conflict; no new row
        end
    end

    Note over C,P: Lost ACK is resolved by retrying the same UUID; PostgreSQL decides whether acceptance occurred.
